The surface composition of N-GQDs was analyzed by XPS technique. High resolution C1s spectrum (Fig. 3
                        a) exhibited four different kind of peaks centered at 284.6, 286.2, 287 and 287.8eV, corresponding to CC, CN, CO and CN groups, respectively [34,35]. Fig. 3b displayed the binding energy peaks of O1s at 532.5, 533.9 and 534.5eV which were attributed to COH/COC, CO and CO bonds, respectively [36–38]. XPS spectrum of N 1s spectrum showed the existence of pyridinic N (398eV), graphitic N (400.4eV), CN (401.9eV) and N oxides of pyridinic nitrogen (403.1eV) (Fig. 3c) [35,36,39,40]. The elemental composition of N-GQDs was determined by using EDX technique (Fig. 3d). The EDX pattern of N-GQDs confirmed the existence of carbon, oxygen and nitrogen in N-GQDs. The elemental analysis of N-GQDs was given in tabular form (Table 1
                        ).
